data.jamchart_notes: One of the finest versions ever played. Incredible and soaring Rick.

data.footnote: Included "Take A Lap" and "Coach on Rainstick" bingo balls. Each band member and Coach took a lap around the barn.
data.jamchart_notes: A first jam that stays within bounds but explodes with the power of the sun leads into a second jam where the band members each have to "Take a Lap". Peter steps out early with aggressive guitar riffing as Rick and the drums lock in on each other as the music takes on a runaway freight train vibe. When Spuds finally takes his turn, Jeff picks up the beat out of the fragmented space and crafts an airy, major-key jam. Coach hops on rainstick and Rick adds some vocalizing as it slowly and patiently winds down.

data.footnote: FTP. Mystery Song #1. Included "15 Minute Jam" bingo ball.
data.jamchart_notes: Mystery Ball #1 for Bingo Tour N1 resulted in what might be considered one of their most epic FTP jams ever due to +15 minute jam bingo ball pulled as song ended. Funky groovy start that turns melodic and once Ben picks up the pace, Rick rips one of his patented, god-like shred peaks.

data.jamchart_notes: Two main segments to this monster. Rick initially crafts a soaring hose motif as he and Peter really lock in on the dual guitars. As the first peak fades away, we are treated to a flamethrower of a ripping jam, going around for more and more builds before finally screaming into the finish. Winner of JOTY 2020.
The legendary HOSEWOOD. Must-hear.
Tender and gorgeous play. Really beautiful stuff.
Encore/Final Song of an incredible show, this is one of the happiest, most melodic, pleasing jams you will hear before a fiery, passionate finish.

data.jamchart_notes: Grippo adds beautifully to the Type I section of the jam. Out of the space, Spuds kicks into a funk groove and the band dives headfirst into a space highly reminiscent of Herbie Hancock. Rick and Grippo trade licks off each other like old friends while Peter saws away at grimy rhythm guitar. Builds in this zone for a while and is a must-hear piece of improv.
